as describes and analyzes the resulting long-term problems this development has posed for Central America. With a new chapter added for the English edition, History and Society in Central America remains vital for readers interested in the region.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 27. Okt 2021) 0aCentral America - Economic integration. 7aHISTORY / Latin America / Central America.2bisacsh1 aBulmer-Thomas, Victor.1 aSullivan-González, Douglass.40uhttps://doi.org/10.7560/78128340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781477306932423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781477306932/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK